-- Global Financial Reform Needed Now, Canadian Bank Chiefs Write in FT
-- John Simpson
-- 2010-04-21T22:43:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-21/global-financial-reform-needed-now-canadian-bank-chiefs-write-in-ft.html

          
          
             Global financial reform is needed 
now, the heads of the six major Canadian banks chiefs write in 
the Financial Times.  
 Reforms to the Basel bank capital accords address the core 
concerns, the CEOs write, adding that new trading rules due to 
go into effect at the end of this year will start the process 
of deleveraging the dealers.  
 “There is pressure within the industry for backsliding on 
implementation of the 2010 rules. But we should not delay; we 
should stick to the schedule,” the bank chiefs write.  
 Policymakers now have the chance to “refocus banking on 
economic growth and job creation,” they write. “For this to 
happen, policies must address the root causes of the financial 
crisis.”   
